  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bae\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Windy conditions will further increase - Department of Meteorology",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Department of Meteorology, the prevailing wind conditions in the western and southern coasts and in the southern part of the island are expected to increase today due to the intense southwest monsoon.",
        "Occasional rain is expected over Sabaragamuwa provinces and Kandy and Nuwara Eliya districts.",
        "It is expected to rain several times in Upper and North Western Provinces and Galle and Matara Districts.",
        "Some places in Uva and Eastern provinces may experience rain or thundershowers during afternoon or night.",
        "Occasional gusty winds of 50-60 kmph may occur over western slopes of central hill country, western, southern and northwestern provinces.",
        "The public is advised to take adequate precautions during thunderstorms to minimize damage caused by temporary strong winds and lightning strikes.",
        "As the South West Monsoon is active, occasional strong winds are expected over the western and southern coasts today.",
        "Occasional rain or thundershowers are expected over coastal areas from Puttalam through Colombo and Galle to Ambantota.",
        "Wind will be blowing from West to Southwest direction with wind speed of 30-40 kmph. Wind speed may increase to 50-60 km/h over offshore areas starting at Colombo Pottu through Galle and Hambantota.",
        "Rough to very rough seas are expected offshore from Colombo through Galle and Ambantota to Pottuvil.",
        "The offshore seas from Puttalam to Colombo are moderate to rough. Other seas surrounding the country are expected to be moderate.",
        "Sea waves (about 2.5 \u2013 3.5 m) are likely to increase in the coastal areas from Puttalam to Pottu through Colombo, Galle and Ambantota.",
        "From Puttalam through Colombo and Galle to Matara, there is a possibility of high waves in the coastal areas close to the coast.",
        "Naval and fishing communities engaged in maritime and naval activities in the seas from Colombo to Hambantota via Galle have been requested to be vigilant in this regard."
      ],
